Next, we will solve for the future value of daily investments. We will use this formula for this:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Future value of daily investment}&=\text{Available cash} \times \text{Annuity factor}
\end{aligned}$$

Since there are $14$ days and a daily rate of $0.013\%$, then our future value annuity factor is $14.012$. Substituting the values, we will get:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Future value of daily investment}&=\$828,000 \times 14.012\\[15 pt]
&=\$11,601,936
\end{aligned}$$

The future value of daily investments is $\$11,601,936$
